==\nAlija discovers thousands of bodies of people executed during [[World War II]] in an abandoned mine. His employer, wanting to sell the mine, pressures him to keep quiet, but he risks his job by alerting police.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Boris Cavazza]]\n* [[Jure Henigman]]\n* [[Leon Lu\u010dev]]\n* Tin Marn\n* Marina Redzepovic\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of submissions to the 90th Academy Awards for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n* [[List of Slovenian submissions for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|6213994|The Miner}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Miner, The}}\n[[Category:2017 films]]\n[[Category:2017 drama films]]\n[[Category:Slovenian films]]\n[[Category:Slovene-language films]]\n[[Category:Slovenian drama films]]\n{{Slovenia-film-stub}}\n{{2010s-drama-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2017 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Miner\n| image          = The Miner (film).jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Hanna Antonina Wojcik Slak]]\n| producer       = Sinisa Juricic<br>Miha Knific\n| writer         = Hanna Antonina Wojcik Slak\n| starring       = [[Boris Cavazza]]\n| music          = Am\u00e9lie Legrand<br>[[Damir Imamovic]]\n| cinematography = Matthias Pilz\n| editing        = Vladimir Gojun\n| distributor    = 2i Film\n| released       = {{film date|2017|9|15|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 98 minutes\n| country        = Slovenia\n| language       = Slovene\n| budget         = \n| gross          = $10,252 (Slovenia)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/intl/?id=_fTHEMINER01&country=SI&wk=2017W41&id=_fTHEMINER01&p=.htm|title=The Miner |work=[[Box Office Mojo]] |accessdate=30 October 2017}}</ref> \n}}\n\n'''''The Miner''''' ({{lang-sl|'''Rudar'''}}) is a 2017 Slovenian [[drama film]] directed by [[Hanna Antonina Wojcik Slak]]. It was selected as the Slovenian entry for the [[Academy Award for Best