{"title_page": "Rugal (TV series)", "text_new": "<noinclude>{{User:RMCD bot/subject notice|1=Rugal|2=Talk:Rugal (TV series)#Requested move 14 April 2020 }}\n</noinclude>{{Short description|2020 South Korean television series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Rugal\n| image                    = Rugal poster.jpg\n| caption                  = Promotional poster\n| native_name              = {{Infobox name module|hangul=\ub8e8\uac08}}\n| genre                    = {{ubl|[[Thriller (genre)|Thriller]]|[[Action film|Action]]|[[Crime]]}}\n| creator                  = \n| based_on                 = ''Rugal'' by Rilmae\n| developer                = \n| writer                   = Do Hyun\n| director                 = Kang Cheol-woo\n| starring                 = {{ubl|[[Choi Jin-hyuk]]|[[Park Sung-woong]]|[[Park Sun-ho]]|[[Jo Dong-hyuk]]|Jung Hye-in|Kim Min-sang}}\n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \n| endtheme                 = \n| composer                 = \n| country                  = South Korea\n| language                 = Korean\n| num_episodes             = 16\n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = \n| producer                 = \n| location                 = \n| cinematography           = \n| editor                   = \n| camera                   = [[Single-camera]]\n| runtime                  = 60 minutes\n| company                  = {{ubl|[[Studio Dragon]]|LIAN Entertainment}}\n| distributor              = {{ubl|[[Orion Cinema Network|OCN]]}}\n| network                  = [[Orion Cinema Network|OCN]]\n| picture_format           = [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n| audio_format             = [[Dolby Digital]]\n| first_run                = \n| first_aired              = March 28, 2020\n| last_aired               = present\n| preceded_by              = <!-- Should not be used to indicate a program that preceded another in a television lineup. -->\n| followed_by              = <!-- Should not be used to indicate a program that followed another in a television lineup. -->\n| related                  = <!-- To be used only for remakes, spin-offs, and adaptations -->\n| website                  = http://program.tving.com/ocn/watcher\n}}\n\n'''''Rugal''''' ({{Korean|\ub8e8\uac08||Lugal}}) is a 2020 [[Korean drama|South Korean television drama]] directed by Kang Cheol Woo, starring [[Choi Jin-hyuk]], [[Park Sung-woong]], [[Park Sun-ho]], Jung Hye-in, [[Jo Dong-hyuk]], [[Han Ji-sang|Han Ji Wan]] and Kim Min-sang. ''Rugal'' is based on the [[webtoon]] of the same name by Rilmae, which was first published in October 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.intronews.net/news/articleView.html?idxno=406702|title=(OCN \ub8e8\uac08) \uc4f0\ub7ec\uc9c4 \ubc15\uc131\uc6c5! \uce58\uba85\uc801 \uc77c\uaca9 \ub0a0\ub9b0 \ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601, \ub9c8\uce68\ub0b4 \ubcf5\uc218 \uc2dc\uc791|date=2020-04-13|website=\uc778\ud2b8\ub85c\ub274\uc2a4|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> The first episode series was aired on Mar 28, 2020, on [[Orion Cinema Network|OCN Network]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://star.hankookilbo.com/News/Read/202004111005051679|title=\u2018\ub8e8\uac08\u2019 \ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601\u2192\uc870\ub3d9\ud601, \ub354 \uac15\ub825\ud574\uc9c4 4\u4eba \ud300\ud50c\ub808\uc774\u2026\uc0c8 \ubbf8\uc158 \ub098\uc120\ub2e4|website=\ud55c\uad6d\uc77c\ubcf4|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> It also airs on [[Netflix]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kof.inven.co.kr/dataninfo/fighter/?code=21200|title=\ud0b9 \uc624\ube0c \ud30c\uc774\ud130 \uc62c\uc2a4\ud0c0 \uc778\ubca4 - AS \ubc14\ub2e5\uc744 \ubaa8\ub974\ub294 \uc695\ub9dd\uc758 \ub8e8\uac08|website=kof.inven.co.kr|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.joins.com/article/23562272|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5]\ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601\u00b7\ubc15\uc131\uc6c5, OCN '\ub8e8\uac08' \uc8fc\uc778\uacf5|last=\uc785\ub825 2019.08.26 17:31|date=2019-08-26|website=\uc911\uc559\uc77c\ubcf4|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newspim.com/news/view/20200327000787|title='\ub8e8\uac08' '\ucee4\ubba4\ub2c8\ud2f0' '\uc624\uc790\ud06c3'\u2026\ub137\ud50c\ub9ad\uc2a4, \uc774\ubc88\uc8fc \uc2e0\uc791 \ub77c\uc778\uc5c5 \uacf5\uac1c|date=2020-03-27|website=\ub274\uc2a4\ud54c|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n== Synopsis ==\nKang Ki-beom ([[Choi Jin-hyuk]]) is an elite police officer whose custody of the Argos, a nationwide criminal organization, results in a group of masked murderers from Argos killing his beloved wife and cutting both eyes. Kang wakes up in a town only to find himself having nothing to do with killing his family members. The NIS approached him as a member of Rugal, an expert team organized by the NIS. He received two artificial eyes with Rugal's biotechnology instructing them and with them unique new studies that would reduce criminal organizations. Kang Ki-beom and Rugal are walking through a life to capture the Argos. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hankyung.com/entertainment/article/202004123422I|title='\ub8e8\uac08' \ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601 \uc8fd\uc774\uae30 \uc704\ud574 \ub098\ud0c0\ub09c \u2018\uc2e4\ud5d8\uccb4\u2019 \uae40\ub2e4\ud604|date=2020-04-12|website=hankyung.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n===Main===\n* [[Choi Jin-hyuk]] as Kang Gi-bum\n* [[Park Sung-woong]] as Hwang Deuk-goo\n* [[Park Sun-ho]] as Lee Gwang-cheol\n* Jung Hye-in as Song Mi-na\n* [[Jo Dong-hyuk]] as Han Tae-woong\n* Kim Min-sang as Choi Geun-cheol\n* Han Ji Wan as Choi Ye-won\n\n===Supporting===\n* [[Jang In-sub]] as Bradley, Rugal's mechanic.\n* Jang Seo-kyung as Susan\n* Park Choong-seon as Section Chief Oh\n* Yoo Sang-hoon as Min Dal-ho, Argos acting leader.\n* Park Jung-hak as Go Yong-deok, assemblyman.\n* Kim In-woo as Choi Yong\n* Yoo Ji-yeon as Jang Mi-joo\n* Ji Dae-han as Bong Man-cheol\n* [[Kim Da-hyun]] as Seol Min-joon\n* Lee Bo-hyun as Yang Moon-bok\n* Lee Seo-el as Yeo-jin,  Kang Gi-bum's wife.\n* Dong Hyun-bae as Lee Jae-han\n* Kim So-ri as singer\n\n==Ratings==\nIn this table, {{color|blue|'''the blue numbers'''}} represent the lowest ratings and {{color|red|'''the red numbers'''}} represent the highest ratings.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! rowspan=\"3\" |{{abbr|Ep.|Episode}}\n! rowspan=\"3\" |Original broadcast date\n! colspan=\"2\" |Average audience share\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |AGB Nielsen<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nielsenkorea.co.kr/tv_terrestrial_day.asp?menu=Tit_1&sub_menu=3_1&area=00|title=Nielsen Korea|work=AGB Nielsen Media Research|language=ko|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160601140426/http://www.nielsenkorea.co.kr/tv_terrestrial_day.asp?menu=Tit_1&sub_menu=3_1&area=00|archive-date=June 1, 2016|accessdate=July 6, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! width=\"90\" |Nationwide\n! width=\"90\" |[[Seoul Capital Area|Seoul]]\n|-\n!1\n|March 28, 2020\n|2.612%\n|2.781%\n|-\n!2\n|March 29, 2020\n|'''{{Color|red|3.884%}}'''\n|4.075%\n|-\n!3\n|April 4, 2020\n|2.874%\n|3.206%\n|-\n!4\n|April 5, 2020\n|3.199%\n|3.879%\n|-\n!5\n|April 11, 2020\n|'''{{Color|blue|2.002%}}'''\n|{{N/A}}\n|-\n!6\n|April 12, 2020\n|2.804%\n|3.437% \n|-\n!7\n|April 18, 2020\n| \n| \n|-\n!8\n|April 19, 2020\n| \n| \n|-\n!9\n|April 25, 2020\n| \n| \n|-\n!10\n|April 26, 2020\n| \n| \n|-\n!11\n|May 2, 2020\n| \n| \n|-\n!12\n|May 3, 2020\n| \n| \n|-\n!13\n|May 9, 2020\n| \n| \n|-\n!14\n|May 10, 2020\n| \n| \n|-\n!15\n|May 16, 2020\n| \n| \n|-\n!16\n|May 17, 2020\n| \n| \n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |Average\n| \n| \n|}\n\n== References ==\n<small class=\"text-muted\"></small>\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://program.tving.com/ocn/rugal}} {{in lang|ko}}\n* {{Hancinema drama|Rugal}}\n* {{IMDb title|tt11769798}}\n\n{{OCN original series}}\n{{Works by Studio Dragon}}\n\n[[Category:Orion Cinema Network television dramas]]\n[[Category:Korean-language television programs]]\n[[Category:2020s South Korean television series]]\n[[Category:2020 South Korean television series debuts]]\n<!-- [[Category:2020 South Korean television series endings]] -->\n[[Category:South Korean thriller television series]]\n[[Category:South Korean action television series]]\n[[Category:South Korean crime television series]]\n[[Category:Television programs based on South Korean webtoons]]\n[[Category:Korean-language Netflix original programming]]\n[[Category:Television series by Studio Dragon]]\n", "text_old": "<noinclude>{{User:RMCD bot/subject notice|1=Rugal|2=Talk:Rugal (TV series)#Requested move 14 April 2020 }}\n</noinclude>{{Short description|2020 South Korean television series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Rugal\n| image                    = Rugal poster.jpg\n| caption                  = Promotional poster\n| native_name              = {{Infobox name module|hangul=\ub8e8\uac08}}\n| genre                    = {{ubl|[[Thriller (genre)|Thriller]]|[[Action film|Action]]|[[Crime]]}}\n| creator                  = \n| based_on                 = ''Rugal'' by Rilmae\n| developer                = \n| writer                   = Do Hyun\n| director                 = Kang Cheol-woo\n| starring                 = {{ubl|[[Choi Jin-hyuk]]|[[Park Sung-woong]]|[[Park Sun-ho]]|[[Jo Dong-hyuk]]|Jung Hye-in|Kim Min-sang}}\n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \n| endtheme                 = \n| composer                 = \n| country                  = South Korea\n| language                 = Korean\n| num_episodes             = 16\n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = \n| producer                 = \n| location                 = \n| cinematography           = \n| editor                   = \n| camera                   = [[Single-camera]]\n| runtime                  = 60 minutes\n| company                  = {{ubl|[[Studio Dragon]]|LIAN Entertainment}}\n| distributor              = {{ubl|[[Orion Cinema Network|OCN]]}}\n| network                  = [[Orion Cinema Network|OCN]]\n| pict